50|$|Within the years, liminal times include {{equinoxes}} when day {{and night}} have equal length, and solstices, when the increase of day or night shifts over to its decrease. Where the <b>Quarter</b> <b>days</b> are held to mark the change in seasons, they also are liminal times.|$|R
50|$|In British and Irish tradition, the <b>quarter</b> <b>days</b> {{were the}} four dates in {{each year on}} which {{servants}} were hired, school terms started, and rents were due. They fell on four religious festivals roughly three months apart {{and close to the}} two solstices and two equinoxes.|$|R
